The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Friday, February 04, 2005 

 Dancing Banderas in new film

 Antonio Banderas

 Los Angeles, Feb. 3 (Reuters): Antonio Banderas is putting on his dance shoes for Take the Lead, inspired by the true story of an international ballroom dancer.

 Banderas will play Pierre Dulane, a former professional dancer who volunteers to teach in the New York public school system. When his ballroom methods clash with his students? hip-hop instincts, he teams up with them to create a new style of dance and becomes their mentor in the process.

 The project is set up at New Line, which originally acquired the rights to Dulane?s story in 2002. He also was the subject of the hit Slamdance festival documentary Mad Hot Ballroom, which recently was acquired by Paramount Classics.

 Shooting starts on April 25 in Toronto. Liz Friedlander is directing.

 Banderas most recently voiced the character of Puss in Boots in Shrek 2 and starred in the HBO movie And Starring Pancho Villa as Himself. He next stars in Legend of Zorro, set for release in November.




